  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Digital Solution Engineer (Valve)",
  "description": "<p><strong>About our client</strong>: Our client is in Automation & Technology, offering process control, industrial software, and digital solutions for industries like Energy, Chemicals, Life Sciences, Oil & Gas, and Marine.<br /></p><p><strong>About the role</strong>:</p><p><strong>1) Business Growth & Engagement</strong></p><ul><li>Identify and develop new PRV monitoring opportunities, partnering with country sales teams to expand the customer base. Understand customer pain points and create value propositions addressing operational challenges. Build strong relationships with key stakeholders, guiding them through technical discussions and solution presentations.</li></ul><p><strong>2) Solution Delivery & Execution</strong></p><ul><li>Develop in-depth product and application knowledge to conduct solution demonstrations and installations.Lead opportunities from initial engagement to delivery and commissioning, ensuring smooth execution via cross-functional collaboration.</li></ul><p><strong>3) Market Insights & Enablement</strong></p><ul><li>Monitor market trends, competitor activities, and industry developments to maintain competitive solutions.Support sales with product training and implementation of business unit strategies.Track and report regional opportunities, challenges, and support needs to drive continuous improvement.</li></ul><p><strong>About you:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Engineering with at least 5 years of experience in the process control industry and instrumentation systems.</li><li>Strong knowledge of measurement instrumentation and valve products; experience with pressure relief valves is an advantage.</li><li>Excellent analytical and questioning skills with the ability to develop and implement strategies.</li><li>Innovative and creative thinker with solid commercial/business understanding.</li><li>Strong analytical mindset and problem-solving abilities.</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</li></ul><p><strong>Other:</strong></p><ul><li>Work location: Jurong West</li><li>Work hours: Monday to Friday</li></ul><p>*Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.*</p><p><br />Employment Agency: Kingsforce Management Services Pte. Ltd.</p><p>Employment Agency Licence No: 94C3545</p><p>EA Personnel: Kimberly Wong | EA Personnel Reg. No.: R1984508</p>",
